04/03/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Council of Europe Secretary General Walter Schwimmer met Foreign Minister Tonino Picula in Zagreb on Monday (3 March) to discuss Croatia's recently submitted application for EU membership. Schwimmer said his visit also tackled regional issues and international efforts concerning Iraq. He stressed the positive impact Croatian integration in the EU would have on other countries in the region. After the meeting, Picula noted the key role the Council of Europe has played in all transition countries in Europe. (HINA, HRT - 03/03/03)
